Apple acquired Beats in 2014, and the popular headphone brand has recently pushed into a few other product categories, including <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2024/09/09/apple-beats-iphone-16-cases/">iPhone cases</a> and charging cables. Apple also <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2024/06/25/beats-pill-bluetooth-speaker-announced/">re-released a Beats Pill portable speaker</a> last year.<div class="linkback">Tags: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-store/">Apple Store</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/beats/">Beats</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/04/17/beats-cables-now-in-apple-stores/">Beats Cables Now Available at Apple Stores</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/beats-cables-now-available-at-apple-stores.2455528/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>